    json: '{"code":{"html":"<div class=\'todo-list\'>\\n  <h2>Todo List</h2>\\n  <input type=\'text\' id=\'todoInput\' placeholder=\'Add new todo\'>\\n  <button onclick=\'addTodo()\'>Add</button>\\n  <ul id=\'todoItems\'>\\n    <!-- Dynamic todo items will be added here -->\\n  </ul>\\n</div>","css":":root {\\n  --primary-color: #4CAF50;\\n  --secondary-color: #f4f4f4;\\n  --input-padding: 10px;\\n  --button-padding-y: 10px;\\n  --button-padding-x: 20px;\\n  --button-border-radius: 5px;\\n  --list-item-padding: 10px;\\n  --list-item-margin-bottom: 5px;\\n  --border-radius: 5px;\\n}\\n\\n.todo-list {\\n  max-width: 100%;\\n  width: 400px;\\n  margin: 0 auto;\\n  padding: 20px;\\n  background-color: var(--secondary-color);\\n  border-radius: var(--border-radius);\\n}\\n\\n.todo-list h2 {\\n  color: var(--primary-color);\\n  text-align: center;\\n}\\n\\ntodo-list input[type=\'text\'] {\\n  width: calc(100% - 20px); /* Account for padding */\\n  padding: var(--input-padding);\\n  margin: 10px 0;\\n  box-sizing: border-box;\\n}\\n\\ntodo-list button {\\n  background-color: var(--primary-color);\\n  color: white;\\n  padding: var(--button-padding-y) var(--button-padding-x);\\n  border: none;\\n  cursor: pointer;\\n  width: calc(100% - 40px); /* Account for padding */\\n  border-radius: var(--button-border-radius);\\n}\\n\\ntodo-list button:hover {\\n  opacity: 0.8;\\n}\\n\\ntodo-list ul {\\n  list-style-type: none;\\n  padding: 0;\\n}\\n\\ntodo-list li {\\n  padding: var(--list-item-padding);\\n  background-color: white;\\n  margin-bottom: var(--list-item-margin-bottom);\\n  border-radius: var(--border-radius);\\n}","js":"function addTodo() {\\n}"},"solution":{"html":"<div class=\'todo-list\'>\\n  <h2>Todo List</h2>\\n  <input type=\'text\' id=\'todoInput\' placeholder=\'Add new todo\'>\\n  <button onclick=\'addTodo()\'>Add</button>\\n  <ul id=\'todoItems\'>\\n    <!-- Dynamic todo items will be added here -->\\n  </ul>\\n</div>","css":":root {\\n  --primary-color: #4CAF50;\\n  --secondary-color: #f4f4f4;\\n  --input-padding: 10px;\\n  --button-padding-y: 10px;\\n  --button-padding-x: 20px;\\n  --button-border-radius: 5px;\\n  --list-item-padding: 10px;\\n  --list-item-margin-bottom: 5px;\\n  --border-radius: 5px;\\n}\\n\\n.todo-list {\\n  max-width: 100%;\\n  width: 400px;\\n  margin: 0 auto;\\n  padding: 20px;\\n  background-color: var(--secondary-color);\\n  border-radius: var(--border-radius);\\n}\\n\\n.todo-list h2 {\\n  color: var(--primary-color);\\n  text-align: center;\\n}\\n\\ntodo-list input[type=\'text\'] {\\n  width: calc(100% - 20px); /* Account for padding */\\n  padding: var(--input-padding);\\n  margin: 10px 0;\\n  box-sizing: border-box;\\n}\\n\\ntodo-list button {\\n  background-color: var(--primary-color);\\n  color: white;\\n  padding: var(--button-padding-y) var(--button-padding-x);\\n  border: none;\\n  cursor: pointer;\\n  width: calc(100% - 40px); /* Account for padding */\\n  border-radius: var(--button-border-radius);\\n}\\n\\ntodo-list ul {\\n  list-style-type: none;\\n  padding: 0;\\n}\\n\\ntodo-list li {\\n  padding: var(--list-item-padding);\\n  background-color: white;\\n  margin-bottom: var(--list-item-margin-bottom);\\n  border-radius: var(--border-radius);\\n}","js":"function addTodo() {\\n  var todoInput = document.getElementById(\'todoInput\');\\n  var todoItems = document.getElementById(\'todoItems\');\\n  var li = document.createElement(\'li\');\\n  li.appendChild(document.createTextNode(todoInput.value));\\n  todoItems.appendChild(li);\\n  todoInput.value = \'\';\\n}"},"question_and_answer":{"question":"","answer":""},"week":"all","instructions":[{"title":"Task Overview:","content":["In this exercise, you\'re tasked with implementing a function to add new todo items to a list dynamically. You\'ll need to select the input and list elements from the DOM and create new list items based on the input value."]},{"title":"JavaScript Objectives:","content":["Understand how to select elements in the DOM using JavaScript.","Learn to create new DOM elements and set their properties.","Practice adding these elements to the DOM to dynamically update the list."]},{"title":"Key Concepts to Explore:","content":["To complete your task, consider exploring the following JavaScript concepts:","Document Object Model (DOM) manipulation methods such as document.getElementById and document.createElement.","Adding event listeners to handle user input and trigger the function."]}],"events":[],"help":{"description":"","images":[],"usefullCSSProperties":[]},"difficulty":"easy","points":0,"maxPoints":5,"percentageTreshold":90,"percentageFullPointsTreshold":98,"accuracy":0,"interactive":false,"showModelPicture":false,"showHotkeys":false,"showScenarioModel":false,"lockHTML":true,"lockCSS":true,"lockJS":false,"scenarios":[{"scenarioId":"z1gh3","dimensions":{"width":300,"height":300},"accuracy":0,"js":""}],"timeData":{"startTime":0,"pointAndTime":{}},"confettiSprinkled":false,"completed":"no","buildingBlocks":{"colors":["#4CAF50","#f4f4f4"]}}'
